{
  "text": "Chapter 14, on pornography's links to rape, is largely anecdotal and lacks data, but is stronger than some others. However, there is a citation of a long-ago correlational study [CITATION_1] that falsely linked reported state rape rates with sales of Playboy, etc., an outcome that was an artifact of state-differences in percentages of young males.",
